article.headline: Paul Quinn 80, Alabama A&M 72
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Rickey Gibson scored 23 points, including five 3-pointers to lead Division II Stillman to a 80-72 win over Alabama A&M Saturday night. Stillman (2-1) came from behind after Alabama A&M had taken a 33-27 halftime lead. Monyea Pratt scored 20 points and had 12 rebounds for Stillman. Joe Martin had 14 points and 12 rebounds for Alabama A&M (0-1). Marcus Jones had 13 points for the Bulldogs, while Michael Ford had 12 and Obie Trotter 10.
